This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the visual features used by humans and machines for object recognition. Additionally, the paper involves a web-based game for identifying these features, which falls under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. The use of Deep Convolutional Networks (DCNs) also suggests that the paper could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
